rol-exploitation persist, with traffickers adapting to evade law enforcement. Differences: Past methods were localized, high-risk, and physically intensive with limited scale; modern methods are global, technology-enabled, lower physical risk for perpetrators, highly scalable, and harder to detect due to anonymity and remote capabilities. Past emphasized physical force; modern prioritizes psychological/digital manipulation. Technologies shifted from manual tools to digital platforms, expanding market size while complicating interventions."
